# diagrams / Excalidraw (@excalidraw/utils)

Excalidraw stores diagrams as a deterministic, version-controllable `.excalidraw` JSON document —
a flat `elements[]` array of hand-drawn-style shapes plus an `appState`. This wrapper authors that
JSON and renders it to SVG headlessly via the community `@swiftlysingh/excalidraw-cli` (MIT), which
bundles fonts and a DOM shim so it runs on macOS with no browser. Pin `seed`/`versionNonce` for
byte-stable output.

controls do
  diagrams.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
end

## Required reading
- [Excalidraw Export Utilities — developer docs](https://docs.excalidraw.com/docs/@excalidraw/excalidraw/api/utils/export) (official, MIT — Excalidraw)
- [`@excalidraw/utils` — npm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@excalidraw/utils) (official, MIT — Excalidraw / excalidraw GitHub org)
- [excalidraw-render-mcp](https://github.com/bassimeledath/excalidraw-render-mcp) (community — bassimeledath)
- No official Anthropic/Claude skill exists for Excalidraw as of 2026-06.

## Render
```bash
npm install -g @swiftlysingh/excalidraw-cli
# author diagram.excalidraw, then:
excalidraw-cli convert diagram.excalidraw --format svg --output diagram.svg
# raster: excalidraw-cli convert diagram.excalidraw --format png --scale 2 --output diagram.png
```

## Failure modes
- Calling `@excalidraw/utils` directly in raw Node fails — it assumes a browser DOM and needs
  jsdom + node-canvas shims. Use the CLI wrapper instead.
- Unpinned `seed`/`versionNonce` produce non-deterministic rough.js jitter — diffs become noisy.
- Missing/wrong element fields (no `seed`, `isDeleted`, `version`) can break rendering — emit the
  full element shape.
- Node < 20.19 not supported by the CLI.
